<br>
Where did that come from? There are only 4 heros and I thought you got the Crown, Mask, Earing, and Choker from them.<br>
<br>
I'm sure the answer is here somewhere, but I missed it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uhyarth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hyarth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/23/01 11:09:30 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Coldain Hero's Insignia Ring **NEW THREAD**</span><hr size=1> Fifth hero is the archer, who is stationary and not controllable. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usamanjah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Samanjah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/23/01 2:05:41 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Coldain Hero's Insignia Ring **NEW THREAD**</span><hr size=1> We did the Peffin part a few days ago with I think a quadruple spawn of the giants surrounding her (it was triple before I turned the note in, I assume another set spawned when Peffin respawned by the fire) ....  It wasn't tough at all -- in fact I had a lvl 52 monk FD pull Peffin, she stayed way seperate from all the giants and I was able to tag her easily and bring her back to the group solo.<br>
<br>
Before I turned the note in I did mess around with trying to harmony all those Kromriff Elites out by the fire and it was a no-go (I am a lvl 60 ranger)...fewest I ever got out of the 18 was 3.<br>
<br>
Samanjah Selassie, 60 Warder<br>
Eternal Jlorjallag, 55 Templar<br>
Cloud of Evolution<br>
The Nameless <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udovewhispersilk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dove Whispersilk</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/24/01 2:10:27 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Coldain Hero's Insignia Ring **NEW THREAD**</span><hr size=1> We attempted the 10th war for the first time on terris today, and after managing to battle through all 3 waves of giants, narandi spawned while we were still finishing off the last 10 or so from the 3rd wave. So one of our druids went and started kiting Narandi arond while we killed the rest of the giants, did rezzes and were buffing up.<br>
<br>
Unfortionatly Narandi despawned in the middle of being kited, and shouted to the zone about how he got away and will come back again someday.<br>
<br>
Just a warning: dont Kite Narandi for too long, as he apparently is on a hard coded despawn timer, doesnt matter if hes aggro or not. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umanr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Manr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/24/01 7:36:36 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Coldain Hero's Insignia Ring **NEW THREAD**</span><hr size=1> Actually NPCs give up after some time if you do not re-aggro them periodically. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uhyarth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hyarth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/24/01 1:17:19 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Coldain Hero's Insignia Ring **NEW THREAD**</span><hr size=1> When we did it, we charged Narandi and had people kite around that last wave of stragglers and then took them out afterwards. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ututmos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tutmos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/24/01 4:08:03 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Coldain Hero's Insignia Ring **NEW THREAD**</span><hr size=1> We've finished the war twice now and just from the text the dorfs give we've always assumed you have to nail Narandi as soon as he spawns. The second war we got beat up on Narandi since people were still beat up from the 3rd wave giants. He sat at the river taking a step every now and then toward the eastern spearmen. As we ressed people up to finish him off he kept heading to the spearmen. I assume he's following whatever pathing the zone has for the spot where we fought him but be careful. If he got any closer we would have agro'd the spearmen and everyone would have been summoned by them while trying to fight Narandi : ).  Just something to watch out for. If you're kiting other waves stay away from the spearmen as well. If you get too close they'll summon the kiter no matter if they've been touched or not. You can't get away once they start to summon you.<br>
<br>
Tutmos Howitzer<br>
Valoran - Karana <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uiustus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iustus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/24/01 6:12:40 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> How to keep the heros alive?</span><hr size=1> I am open to suggestions here.<br>
<br>
My most recent thought was to just summon them all to the opposite end of the zone and keep them out of the fight. This doesnt seem to work so well. They, and their forces seem to run into pathing bugs (or something) which causes them to 32k themselves. I tried this technique last night, taking them near the dwarven mines to the southeast. I know I started with at least 3 heros who made it to me, and at least 20 or so of their forces, but a couple hours later it was down to two and eventually just down to Corbin, with all of his supporting forces gone. Pathing seems to be particularly bad in places, perhaps some people with pets have a suggestion?<br>
<br>
Another idea I have is to have monks (or just use CoH with anyone) agro each of the heros and walk them solo (without their armies) to a safe spot to the south. This would also allow us to get the uncontrolable hero.<br>
<br>
We tried keeping forces with the heros, to kite mobs away from them before they engaged, but that did not seem to work well.<br>
<br>
I would just keep the heros with the main forces if it was not for all the extra lag and LDs that all those dwarven npcs running around causes. (That IS what we did the very first time, for lack of knowing what would happen, but we lost heros).<br>
<br>
Perhaps the best thing is the simplest. Go back to what we tried before, but pick better people to do it. Station enough people to do kiting that the heros should never see battle.<br>
<br>
-Iustus <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uinterslayer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>InterSlayer</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/24/01 9:03:56 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Coldain Hero's Insignia Ring **NEW THREAD**</span><hr size=1> If you're gonna do the quest...<br>
<br>
try printing out the most accurate map you can of GD and have pple scout and shout locs of major areas like where the heroes are, and where the waves of giants start. T<br>
<br>
hat way we can at least pin point locs and work on some kind of battle strategy =D <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubaven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Baven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/24/01 9:11:16 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Coldain Hero's Insignia Ring **NEW THREAD**</span><hr size=1> Iustus:<br>
<br>
Training heros doesn't work. We tried that on Xev and what we got was 3rd wave &quot;Seneschal shouts, They have reached the city&quot; you lose, all depops.<br>
<br>
You have to keep the giants away from the city as well as seneschal alive. Got it tonight though with alot of kiting <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Nenja<br>
Harmonium-Xev<br>
www.harmonium.net <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uiustus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iustus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/24/01 11:29:49 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Coldain Hero's Insignia Ring **NEW THREAD**</span><hr size=1> I dont mean kiting the Seneschal. Protect him. My problem is the other 5 pieces of loot you get if the 5 heros (Gardain, Dobbin, Churn, Corbin and the archer) survive, but these heros are lvl 45 and die pretty fast, usually because they cannot stay out of trouble. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
The problem with just using the scout to order them to safety seems to be that because of bad pathing they 32k themselves.<br>
<br>
I think what we will probably do is have someone pull each one of these to a safe spot in the south and then hand them off to a single kiter (using FD/CoH). Once all 5 of the heros are safely following this one kiter, the others can return to the battle. When Narandi spawns, they despawn, and the kiter can return to fight Naradni.<br>
<br>
The other advantage of this is the person controlling the scout can continue to give orders to the remaining forces even though the heros are not with them.<br>
<br>
The disadvantage is all four (or perhaps five) heros will be constantly spamming the zone with their agro messages.<br>
<br>
The other leading idea is to just try to keep the dwarven forces in place with enough people around them to kite giants away before they are engaged. Since that is what I tried last time, and it failed, I am reluctant to try it again, as it relies too much on too many people to not mess up.<br>
<br>
-Iustus <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udargathikithkanan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dargathi Kithkanan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/25/01 10:02:44 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Coldain Hero's Insignia Ring **NEW THREAD**</span><hr size=1> Firstly fantastic work to all involved in breaking this quest. Well done all..<br>
<br>
Secondly I'm looking for lots of info, know your enemy...<br>
<br>
Remember, I havent seen this, so please feel free to dismiss any comments fully and without prejudice<br>
<br>
Exact (or as near as dammit) /locs for each of the forces in this<br>
<br>
Coldain forces starting positions and numbers.<br>
Giant Spawn positions and Directions of travel<br>
Number of waves, number of giants per wave<br>
And Named Giants spawn position and direction of travel.<br>
Wave spawn conditions.. (Are all the waves timed, or does one wave not spawn till the preceding wave is destroyed.<br>
<br>
The first thing to remember is there are two goals here.<br>
<br>
1) Kill the named Giant<br>
2) Keep as many named Coldain alive as possible.<br>
<br>
Now to some ideas<br>
<br>
At the start of the battle, the quester calls all the Coldain to him, and keeps em there, make up one hotkey calling them all. this removes all the coldain from the battle.<br>
<br>
Ok so now you have to deal with all the giants with just players.. sound impossible?<br>
<br>
If each wave can be tagged by a kiter, then passed on to another, kinda like chain kiting it should in theory be possible to get one kite team with all the primary waves on them. hence removing them from the battle equasion completely. perhaps a few lower levl groups to peal off the giants one at a time...<br>
<br>
So now all that has to be worried about is the named, and his bodyguards (warlords)<br>
<br>
This should in theory be as simple as any other multi FD split.<br>
<br>
To clarify, assuming there are 11 giants total, 1 named and 10 warlords.<br>
<br>
So you allocate each monk/SK/necro to grab 2 mobs. they take em as far away as they can, and FD.<br>
<br>
To maintain the split the FD team pop before the giants are too far away from them, to maintain agro, then go down when the giants are close again, again, isolating this bunch of Giants out of the battle completely.<br>
<br>
Then the named can be taken out by whatever force is required to do this.<br>
<br>
Now I know much of this is based on supposition, however when facing an unknown opponant the first formation of any plan needs to be as simple as possible.<br>
<br>
